{
  "texts": [
    "Our initial SHAP results for hypertension included some blood pressure medications with high SHAP values that may indicate patients missing a diagnosis code in our dataset.",
    "These should have been filtered out by the cohort selection process but had been missed due to data quality issues (e.g., alternative spellings, coding errors, or missing links to medication categories).",
    "After consultation with clinicians, these patients were removed from the dataset and the model was retrained.",
    "This reduced the validation performance of the model slightly (from 0.924 to 0.922 ROC AUC) as these patients had evidently been easier to classify.",
    "Explainability analysis conducted during model development may therefore prevent data quality issues in EHR data from leading to overly optimistic estimates of model performance."
  ]
}